# Firm Investment Criteria

> Remove the `.example` extension to activate. These settings override
> the defaults in `references/investment-criteria.md`.

## Dimension Weights

Adjust weights to reflect your firm's investment thesis. Must sum to 100.

| Dimension  | Weight | Notes                              |
| ---------- | ------ | ---------------------------------- |
| Market     | 30     | We are thesis-driven, market-first |
| Team       | 25     | Founders matter at seed            |
| Product    | 20     | Must have working prototype        |
| Financials | 15     | Early-stage, revenue optional      |
| Timing     | 10     | Why now matters                    |

## Scoring Thresholds

| Score Range | Decision    |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| 75-100      | Strong Pass |
| 60-74       | Discuss     |
| 40-59       | Weak Pass   |
| 0-39        | Pass        |

## Focus Areas

### Target Stages

- Seed, Pre-Seed

### Target Sectors

- Enterprise SaaS
- Developer Tools
- AI/ML Infrastructure

### Check Size

- $250K - $1M

## Red Flags (Automatic Score Reduction)

- No technical co-founder (-15 points)
- Single founder (-10 points)
- Pre-revenue with >$2M raise (-10 points)
- Crowded market without clear differentiation (-10 points)
- Regulatory risk without mitigation plan (-10 points)

## Green Flags (Score Boost)

- Repeat founder with prior exit (+10 points)
- >$10K MRR at seed (+10 points)
- Strong open-source traction (+5 points)
- Notable angel investors (+5 points)
